This is a central location for the core definitions for components of the \mu HOL^{ex} cyclic proof system.
  283mhe-0005mhe-0005.xml\mu HOL^{ex} domain syntaxDefinition2024123Chris Purdy
Domains/types in \mu HOL^{ex} are defined as follows, where D ranges over a countable set of base domains, and v ranges over the set \{+, -, \star \} of variance annotations.
       \begin {align*}       S, T &::= D\ |\ S \to ^v T\\       P &::= \text {Prop}\ |\ T \to ^v P     \end {align*}   
  The base domains would be specified in a signature.
  285mhe-0004mhe-0004.xml\mu HOL^{ex} formula syntaxDefinition2024123Chris Purdy
The syntax of \mu HOL^{ex} formulae has a small logical fragment, extended with a fixed-point operator, variance annotations and contraints for ordinal variables. v ranges over variance annotations, and P, T range over predicate and non-predicate domains respectively.
       t ::=\ x\ |\ \forall  (x : T).t\ |\ t \Rightarrow  t^\prime \ |\ \lambda (x^v : T).t\ |\ t\ t^\prime \ |\ \mu ^\alpha (x:P).t\ |\ \exists \alpha .t\ |\ \beta  < \alpha    
  287mhe-0002mhe-0002.xmlVariance typing system for \mu HOL^{ex} formulae2024122Chris Purdy
